# GitHub Pages Deployment

This project is deployed to GitHub Pages using the **legacy** (branch-based) mode.
The built app is committed to the `docs/` directory on `main`, and GitHub serves it directly.

## How It Works

src/ → npm run build → dist/ → copy to docs/ → push to main → GitHub Pages serves docs/

- `dist/` is gitignored (local build artifact)
- `docs/` is committed (GitHub Pages source)
- `.nojekyll` in `docs/` disables Jekyll processing
- Live URL: https://xiaoyu727.github.io/Prototype_Activation_Tracker/

## Agent Instructions

A **pre-commit hook** automatically rebuilds `docs/` whenever source files are staged.
Do NOT manually rebuild `docs/` — the hook handles it during `git commit`.

### If the hook is missing

Git hooks are not tracked by git and can be lost after a re-clone. If `git commit`
does not produce "Rebuilding docs/ for GitHub Pages..." output, reinstall the hook:

```bash
cat > .git/hooks/pre-commit << 'HOOK'
#!/bin/sh
STAGED=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=d | grep -v '^docs/')
if [ -z "$STAGED" ]; then exit 0; fi
echo "Rebuilding docs/ for GitHub Pages..."
npm run build && rm -rf docs && cp -r dist docs && touch docs/.nojekyll
git add docs/
echo "docs/ updated."
HOOK
chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit
```
